The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 6: Air India has announced heavy discounts on first and business class international tickets and a 10 per cent cut in the base fare on any ticket booked on its website. A 50 per cent discount will be available on the highest market basic fare for first-class travel to the US, Canada, UK, Europe, Tokyo, Jeddah and Riyadh, an airline release said.                            
	 Mumbai, March 6: The Bank of India (BoI) has tied up with Reliance Mutual Fund to distribute and market the latters products through its branches. The bank will use its pan-India network of over 3,000 branches to sell the products.                             
	 Calcutta, March 6: ITC today said a hike in cigarette prices was inevitable because of the imposition of excise duty on tobacco in the budget. While the effective rates of taxation on cigarettes prior to the budget was 190 per cent, it (the budget) had imposed another 17 per cent excise duty hike.                                                                                                                          
